<tr><td><font face="Arial, Geneva" size="+1">
<br><br>
<strong>The innovative authentication system</strong>
</font></td></tr>
<tr><td><font face="Arial, Geneva" size="-1">
<blockquote>
The A-Select Authentication System (in short A-Select) is an open source innovative system for authentication of users in a Web environment. A-Select is a framework where users can be authenticated by several means with Authentication Service Providers (AuthSP's). <br>

Several AuthSP's have been implemented already and are used in pilot projects. Among them, very strong AuthSP's like ABN AMRO Internet Banking, Rabobank Internet banking and SURFkey Bank/SMS (former Niegefoon/Mob@c) are in use in pilot projects. But also more commonly used AuthSP's are implemented like Radius and LDAP. A-Select will constantly be extended with more (new) AuthSP's.<br><br>
A-Select is an open source project that originally has been designed and implemented by <a href="http://www.alfa-ariss.com" target="_blank">Alfa & Ariss </a>.<br>
<br><br>

A-Select is part of the National Science Foundation Middleware Initiative (NMI) <a href="http://www.nmi-edit.org/">EDIT</a> software release.<a href="http://www.nsf-middleware.org/"><img src="/images/NMI_n03.png" height="25" border="0" ALT="NMI Logo" VALIGN="center"></a>
<br><br><br><br>

If you are planning an A-Select roll-out and 
for questions regarding development and innovation on the A-Select Middleware platform, please contact Bart Kerver: <a href="mailto:bart.kerver@ictu.nl">bart.kerver@ictu.nl</a>
</blockquote>
</font></td></tr>
</tr>
</table>
